04459nam a22007095i 9781463242664DE-B159720220302035458.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220302t20212021nju    fo  d z      eng d  a2021030515  a97814632426647 a10.31826/97814632426642doi  a(DE-B1597)606792  a(OCoLC)1260171321  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anjucUS-NJ00aBS1938b.S73 2021 4aBS1938b.S73 2021 7aREL0061002bisacsh04a225.4/82231 aStanojević, Jovan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aOrthodox New Testament Textual Scholarship :bAntoniades, Lectionaries, and the Catholic Epistles /cJovan Stanojević. 1aPiscataway, NJ : bGorgias Press, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (225 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTexts and Studies (Third Series) ;v2600tFrontmatter -- tTABLE OF CONTENTS -- tABBREVIATIONS -- tPREFACE -- tACKNOWLEDGEMENTS -- tINTRODUCTION -- tCHAPTER ONE. HISTORY AND BACKGROUND OF THE ANTONIADES EDITION -- tCHAPTER TWO. ANTONIADES’ MANUSCRIPTS, WITH SPECIAL REFERENCE TO THE WITNESSES OF THE PRAXAPOSTOLOS -- tCHAPTER THREE. TESTSTELLEN: COLLATION OF THE CATHOLIC EPISTLES -- tCHAPTER FOUR. THE EDITIO CRITICA MAIOR AND ANTONIADES’ TEXT OF THE CATHOLIC EPISTLES -- tCHAPTER FIVE. FINAL REFLECTIONS -- tAPPENDIX: A TRANSLATION OF ANTONIADES’ PREFACE TO HIS EDITION OF THE GREEK NEW TESTAMENT -- tBIBLIOGRAPHY -- tINDICES0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe present study represents the first attempt to expand the methodological and practical framework of textual scholarship on the Greek New Testament from an Orthodox perspective. Its focus is on the Antoniades edition of 1904, commonly known as the Patriarchal Edition. The examination of the creation and reception of this edition shows that its textual principles are often misrepresented. In particular, it is shown to be more closely related to the Textus Receptus than to lectionary manuscripts. This is confirmed by an analysis of lectionary manuscripts using the Text und Textwert methodology and a detailed comparison of the Antoniades edition with the recent Editio Critica Maior of the Catholic Epistles. A textual commentary is provided on key verses in order to formulate guidelines for preparing an edition of the Greek New Testament that would satisfy the needs of Orthodox users in different contexts. This study offers a foundation for the further development of New Testament textual scholarship from an Orthodox perspective, informed both by modern critical scholarship and Orthodox tradition. It also provides a fresh translation of Antoniades’ introduction in an Appendix.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 4aBible. 4aCriticism, Interpretation/New Testament. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / New Testament.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074330240uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324266440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463242664423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463242664/original  a978-3-11-074330-2  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK